Power Menu


 


Power Menu

Version - 1.7


Description


Is your device's power button not working or is it broken?

Don't want to use an extra remote for shutting down android tv box?

Then here's your life and money savior!


Power Menu

Power Menu simulates the action of power button, enabling access to power menu options under critical circumstances.


Features

- Supports all android versions through Android 5.0 (Lollipop)

- Shows power menu options directly on application launch as well as on notification click
(Android 11 and below)

- Adds a floating button at the bottom-right side of the screen, thus revealing power menu options on single click followed by changing of positions and visibility on long press
(Android 12 and above)


Usage of Accessibility API

Power Menu requires accessibility service for showing the power menu options on screen using the default functions and features that are mentioned in 'Accessibility Service'.

Therefore, it's mandatory for Power Menu to use the Accessibility Service API for accessing it's functions or methods as without accessibility service the app won't work.


Instructions

Steps to follow on fresh install -

A) Normal mode

1. Open the app.
2. Tap on the information area to quickly access accessibility settings.
3. Enable 'Power Menu' accessibility service.
4. Do one of the following things -
a) Go back sequentially until the app exits.
b) Press home button and clear the recent apps or clean the memory
cache.
c) Restart the device.

B) Emergency mode

1. After installing app, don't open the app at first glance.
2. Instead head over to the Accessibility settings manually and enable the 'Power Menu' accessibility service first.
3. Then launch the app.
